                <h2>
                    <a href="#">Welcome to our blog</a>
                </h2>
                <hr>
                <p>This is the first in a series of articles that we will publish related to the art of tattoo and tattooing. Each month we will discuss different aspects of the world of tattoo. There is a wide range of information regarding tattooing available in the mainstream media. Some of it is correct; some of it is total foolishness. As the owners of two shops we see a wide range of customers with an equally wide range of requests for tattoos. We see 18-year-old kids looking for their first tattoo as well as older collectors with a wide range of ink seeking a very definite image idea. Some shops are dedicated to producing quality artwork while some shops, unfortunately, are dedicated to making money. Dragon Lily Tattoo’s primary interest is creating beautiful and interesting artwork for our customers. We seek to involve all of our customers in the process of tattoo; we are dedicated to ensuring that each tattoo we do is the best that we can do and it’s the best for the customer.
                <br>
                <br>
                There is a lot of misinformation and misconceptions regarding tattoo and tattooing and we hope to use this blog to clear up and clarify many of these misconceptions. Stay posted and take a look every month as we update the blog entries. These entry’s will include such things as; Choosing a shop, Choosing an artist, How to arrive at the correct and appropriate design, The idea of “Go big or Go home”, Color versus Black and Gray, Custom designed images versus “Flash” or predesigned tattoos, and Lettering pros and cons.
                <br>
                <br>
                If you have any questions, comments or specific topics related to tattooing that you would like to have discussed send as a message via the “contact us” page.
                <br>
                <br>
                Until next time,
